More than 20,000 people from three hunger-stricken constituencies in Kilifi county have received relief food from an international organisation.Sri Sathya Sai Kenya, which has its headquarters in the US, through Mining CS Dan Kazungu on Sunday donated food to residents of Malindi, Magarini and Ganze.Kazungu flagged off caravans at the Malindi deputy county commissioner&rsquo;s office, before overseeing distribution to the starving families.Each beneficiary got four kilogrammes of maize flour, two kilogrammes of beans, one kilogramme of salt, one litre of cooking oil and clothes, including two pairs of shirts and a pair of shorts. Others, however, were not lucky as they were not on the list.The CS thanked the firm for intervening to help the poor.